critical_positive: I think it worked finding a bit about her, and creating conversation that made her feel comfortable talking about. critical_negative: I think the fact that we didn't have much in common made it kind of hard, because there were a couple times where we were both silent, and trying to think of what to talk about. rest_of_day_open: I have a lot of concerns about the rest of my week, because there are many tasks and obligations that I need to complete. critical_positive: The main reason why the conversation went as well as it did is because both of us were willing to fill in the gaps and ask questions of the other party when the current conversation topic petered out. I think that my conversation partner was especially good in this regard, as he was able to come up with new topics or leading questions relatively quickly. He was also able to contribute far  more than enough to the current conversation that I had enough time to prepare to respond or for a topic change.
critical_negative: I had difficulty talking about myself or offering meaningful insights during a couple points during the conversation. Instead, I only said a few sentences worth about myself and my opinions before letting my conversation partner carry the conversation further. Nearing the end of the interaction, I felt that my partner became a lot less engaged and was ready for the chat to be over. While I was also very willing to end it, I do think that I could have done a better job engaging my conversation partner, especially within the last 5 or so minutes.
